to-5%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20being%20at%20the%20office%20from%209-to-5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20no%20standard%20arrival%20or%20departure%20times%2C%20people's%20non-traditional%20commutes%20have%20meant%20we're%20sitting%20in%20traffic%20or%20on%20congested%20trains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnever-ending-rush-hour-remote-work-flexible-schedules-commutes-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eno%20matter%20what%20time%20of%20day%20it%20is%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writes%20BI's%20Juliana%20Kaplan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20distance%20people%20travel%20to%20get%20to%20work%20is%20also%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20which%20could%20be%20why%20they're%20keen%20to%20leave%20the%20office%20early.%20In%202024%2C%209.3%25%20of%20workers%20traveled%20an%20hour%20or%20more%20to%20work%20compared%20to%207.7%25%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20statistic%20seems%20likely%20to%20keep%20rising%20as%20young%20people%20seeking%20affordable%20homes%20move%20farther%20from%20metropolitan%20hubs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20a%20card-carrying%20member%20of%20the%20suburban%20commuters%2C%20I'm%20here%20to%20help.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20got%20a%20roughly%2080-minute%20commute%20that%20includes%20a%20car%2C%20a%20train%2C%20and%20a%20subway.%20Couple%20that%20with%20two%20little%20ones%20at%20home%20and%20a%20spouse%20who%20also%20commutes%2C%20and%20I'm%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20commutemaxxing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20my%20advice%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3EFailure%20to%20prepare%20is%20preparing%20to%20fail%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOutfit%20picked.%20Work%20bag%20packed.%20Gas%20tank%20full.%20Put%20the%20work%20in%20the%20night%20before%20so%20you%20can%20leave%20less%20to%20chance%20the%20morning%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKnow%20the%20ebbs%20and%20flows%20of%20your%20commute%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20know%20what%20time%20I%20need%20to%20turn%20off%20my%20street%20to%20beat%20a%20local%20bus%20that'll%20slow%20me%20down.%20I%20know%20the%20right%20spot%20to%20mobile-order%20my%20Starbucks%20coffee%20so%20it's%20ready%20when%20I%20arrive.%20Turning%20your%20commute%20into%20a%20formula%20might%20only%20save%20you%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20time%2C%20but%20it%20adds%20up%20to%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20leave%20your%20bag%20on%20an%20open%20seat%20in%20a%20crowded%20train%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20isn't%20really%20a%20commuting%20tip.%20I%20just%20hate%20people%20who%20do%20this.%20Don't%20think%20that'll%20stop%20me%20from%20asking%20to%20sit%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20those%20steps%20in%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESneaking%20in%20a%20bit%20more%20walking%20on%20your%20way%20to%20work%20can%20do%20wonders%20for%20your%20fitness%20and%20longevity.%20Maybe%20take%20the%20stairs%20(within%20reason)%20or%20opt%20for%20the%20long%20route%20on%20your%20way%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20run%20for%20that%20train%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20know%20I%20said%20get%20some%20exercise%20in%2C%20but%20not%20like%20this.%20No%20one%20wants%20to%20see%20you%20pull%20a%20hammy%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Grand%20Central%20Terminal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeave%20some%20work%20for%20the%20ride%20home%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENothing%20makes%20a%20commute%20go%20by%20faster%20than%20having%20to%20wrap%20up%20some%20stuff%20on%20the%20train%20ride%20home.%20This%20is%20a%20bit%20trickier%20for%20people%20driving%2C%20but%20maybe%20that's%20where%20AI%20comes%20into%20play.%20Build%20an%20AI%20agent%20that%20you%20can%20dictate%20end-of-day%20tasks%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-advice-to-avoid-nightmare-commute-nyc-rto-wfh-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782128741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a345a7df4bed3c6152cbea0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-advice-to-avoid-nightmare-commute-nyc-rto-wfh-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Flexible%20work%20schedules%20mean%20people%20are%20commuting%20at%20all%20hours%20of%20the%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20turning%20our%20trips%20to%20the%20office%20into%20a%20nightmare.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ddefrancesco%40businessinsider.com%20(Dan%20DeFrancesco)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Legendary%20Fed%20chair%20Alan%20Greenspan%20dies%20at%20100%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alan%20Greenspan%20in%202003%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d9a78c5138e4a2a772826f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221989%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlan%20Greenspan%20led%20the%20Fed%20from%201987%20to%202006.%3Cp%3EStefan%20Zaklin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELegendary%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%20Alan%20Greenspan%20has%20died%20at%20age%20100.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGreenspan%20served%20as%20Fed%20chair%20from%201987%20until%202006%2C%20earning%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BThe%20Maestro.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20helped%20turn%20the%20Fed%20chair%20from%20a%20figure%20of%20relative%20obscurity%20to%20a%20major%20public%20figure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlan%20Greenspan%2C%20the%20legendary%20central%20banker%20who%20led%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades%2C%20has%20died%20at%20100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlan%20passed%20away%20at%20our%20home%20this%20morning%20at%20the%20age%20of%20100%20from%20complications%20of%20Parkinson's%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspan's%20wife%2C%20Andrea%20Mitchell%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20given%20to%20NBC.%20Mitchell%20is%20the%20chief%20Washington%20correspondent%20and%20the%20chief%20foreign%20affairs%20correspondent%20for%20NBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20a%20giant%20of%20a%20man%20who%20helped%20shape%20the%20US%20economy%20for%20decades%20under%20presidents%20of%20both%20parties%2C%20but%20was%20always%20honest%20in%20acknowledging%20his%20mistakes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%20he%20was%20my%20husband%2C%20who%20shaped%20my%20life%20from%20our%20very%20first%20date%20in%201984.%20He%20had%20'irrational%20exuberance'%20for%20baseball%2C%20the%20Washington%20Commanders%2C%20tennis%2C%20golf%20and%20music%2C%20especially%20jazz%2C%26quot%3B%20Mitchell%20added.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EServing%20as%20Fed%20chairman%20from%201987%20to%202006%2C%20Greenspan%20oversaw%20nearly%20two%20decades%20of%20relative%20economic%20strength%2C%20which%20earned%20him%20praise%20and%20eventually%20the%20moniker%20%26quot%3BThe%20Maestro.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20helped%20to%20sustain%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20economic%20growth%20periods%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20through%20his%20deft%20adjustment%20of%20interest%20rates.%20But%20according%20to%20his%20critics%2C%20his%20moves%20also%20overprioritized%20the%20financial%20markets%20and%20sowed%20the%20seeds%20of%20the%20monumental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-greenspan-the-financial-crisis-wasnt-my-fault-2010-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecollapse%20of%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20also%20helped%20elevate%20the%20public%20profile%20of%20the%20position%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F11%2F02%2Fbooks%2Freview%2Falan-greenspan-capitalism-in-america-adrian-wooldridge.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erock%20star%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20label%20from%20the%20media%20%E2%80%94%20and%20increased%20the%20transparency%20of%20the%20Fed.%20After%20leaving%20the%20job%2C%20Greenspan%20consulted%20for%20a%20number%20of%20financial%20firms%20and%20remained%20a%20public%20voice%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20true%20measure%20of%20a%20career%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20be%20content%2C%20even%20proud%2C%20that%20you%20succeeded%20through%20your%20own%20endeavors%20without%20leaving%20a%20trail%20of%20casualties%20in%20your%20wake%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fid%2Fwbna7864194%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%202005%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4164827-6788-4fef-87ea-8b873c095ef3%5C%22%3EFrom%20clarinet%20player%20to%20the%20White%20House%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20was%20born%20in%201926%20in%20the%20Washington%20Heights%20neighborhood%20of%20New%20York%20City%20to%20Herbert%20Greenspan%2C%20a%20stockbroker%2C%20and%20Rose%20Goldsmith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20Greenspan%20learned%20to%20play%20various%20musical%20instruments%2C%20even%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1987%2F06%2F08%2Fbusiness%2Fgreenspan-s-special-talents.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattending%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20prestigious%20Juilliard%20School%20for%20two%20years%20as%20a%20clarinet%20player.%20Greenspan%20was%20rejected%20by%20a%20draft%20board%20in%201944%20due%20to%20a%20spot%20on%20his%20lung%20X-ray%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2007%2F09%2F18%2Fbooks%2F18leonhardt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20spent%20some%20of%20the%20World%20War%20II%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20playing%20clarinet%20for%20bandleader%20Henry%20Jerome's%20ensemble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20war%2C%20Greenspan%20studied%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20where%20he%20earned%20an%20undergraduate%20degree%20in%20economics%20in%201950%20and%20eventually%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB120917419049046805%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenspan's%20dissertation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20pulled%20from%20public%20access%20by%20NYU%20in%201987%20at%20the%20economist's%20request%20and%20became%20a%20source%20of%20speculation%20%E2%80%94%20focused%20in%20part%20on%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20housing%20bubble%2C%20a%20prescient%20topic%20given%20the%20housing%20crisis%20roughly%20three%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20academic%20interests%2C%20Greenspan%20also%20worked%20in%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20first%20at%20The%20National%20Industrial%20Conference%20Board%20%E2%80%94%20a%20think%20tank%20now%20known%20as%20the%20Conference%20Board%20%E2%80%94%20and%20later%20at%20his%20own%20economic%20consulting%20firm%2C%20Townsend-Greenspan%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%2C%20where%20he%20helped%20to%20advise%20major%20corporations%20on%20economic%20trends.%20Greenspan%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deseretnews.com%2Farticle%2F809511%2FUS-Senate-Panel-Votes-for-4th-Term-for-Fed-Chairman-Greenspan.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eserved%20on%20the%20boards%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20slew%20of%20companies%2C%20including%20JPMorgan%2C%20Alcoa%2C%20and%20Mobil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20growing%20his%20private%20business%2C%20Greenspan%20began%20dipping%20his%20toes%20into%20government%20work%20during%20this%20time.%20He%20served%20as%20an%20advisor%20to%20Richard%20Nixon's%201968%20campaign%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F11%2F06%2Fbooks%2Freview%2Falan-greenspan-man-who-knew-sebastian-mallaby.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelped%20with%20sophisticated%20polling%3C%2Fa%3E%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222797%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alan%20greenspan%201974%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3920ed0e60dfb3f373ff7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222098%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlan%20Greenspan%20in%201974%2C%20when%20he%20served%20as%20chairman%20of%20the%20President's%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers.%3Cp%3ECharles%20Kelly%2FAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Greenspan%20did%20not%20take%20a%20formal%20administration%20job%20under%20Nixon%2C%20he%20did%20serve%20as%20an%20outside%20advisor%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fbusiness%2F2006%2F01%2F27%2Fchairman-moved-a-nation-span-classbankheadlong-career-produced-many-victoriesspan%2F9f13e903-b574-48b3-9d48-4b0070581e4f%2F%3Futm_term%3D.609745a0706f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtributed%20to%20various%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20experts.%20In%20particular%2C%20Greenspan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Frand%2Fpubs%2Fmonographs%2FMG265%2Fimages%2FwebS0243.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eserved%20on%20the%20commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20in%201970%2C%20recommended%20ending%20the%20military%20draft%20and%20moving%20to%20an%20all-volunteer%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20did%20eventually%20join%20Gerald%20Ford's%20White%20House%20from%201974%20to%201977%20as%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers.%20During%20Ronald%20Reagan's%20presidency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreservehistory.org%2Fpeople%2Falan_greenspan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenspan%20also%20chaired%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20National%20Commission%20on%20Social%20Security%20Reform%20from%201981%20to%201983%20and%20served%20on%20Reagan's%20Economic%20Policy%20Advisory%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20work%2C%20Greenspan%20married%20his%20first%20wife%2C%20Joan%20Mitchell%2C%20in%201952.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FBusiness%2Fstory%3Fid%3D89300%26page%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarriage%20was%20annulled%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20though%20the%20pair%20remained%20friendly.%20Mitchell%20did%20introduce%20Greenspan%20to%20another%20important%20figure%20in%20the%20economist's%20life%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FBusiness%2Fstory%3Fid%3D89300%26page%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephilosopher%20and%20author%20Ayn%20Rand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20economist%20was%20taken%20with%20Rand's%20ideas%20of%20rugged%20individualism%20and%20free-market%20capitalism.%20Greenspan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2007%2F09%2F15%2Fbusiness%2F15atlas.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20defense%20of%20Rand's%20book%20%26quot%3BAtlas%20Shrugged%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20late%201950s%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitution.org%2F1-Activism%2Fmon%2Fgreenspan_gold.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20handful%20of%20articles%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Rand's%20magazine%20%26quot%3BThe%20Objectivist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Greenspan%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fatlassociety.org%2Fcommentary%2Fcommentary-blog%2F4926-the-alan-greenspan-confession-%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappeared%20to%20distance%20himself%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20some%20aspects%20of%20Rand's%20objectivist%20philosophy%2C%20he%20was%20widely%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20most%20famous%20of%20her%20acolytes%20prior%20to%20becoming%20Fed%20Chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec0076d9-72dc-486f-97ad-e2035d0ace81%5C%22%3E'The%20Maestro'%20takes%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%2C%20a%20lifelong%20Republican%2C%20privately%20advised%20Reagan%20during%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%201980%20presidential%20election%20and%20throughout%20the%20first%20six%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20his%20presidency.%20This%20relationship%20with%20Reagan%20ultimately%20led%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1987%2F06%2F03%2Fbusiness%2Fvolcker-out-after-8-years-as-federal-reserve-chief-reagan-chooses-greenspan.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresident%20to%20select%20the%20economist%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20succeed%20Paul%20Volcker%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20in%201987.%20Greenspan%20would%20then%20go%20on%20to%20become%20the%20second-longest-serving%20Chairman%20in%20history%20and%20was%20renominated%20by%20Presidents%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%2C%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20and%20George%20W.%20Bush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Chairman%2C%20Greenspan%20was%20generally%20credited%20with%20a%20deft%20handling%20of%20monetary%20policy.%20The%20US%20only%20entered%20recessions%20twice%20during%20his%20nearly%2020-year%20run%2C%20after%20averaging%20four%20recessions%20in%20each%20of%20the%20previous%20two%2020-year%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22greenspan%20volcker%20reagan%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5bcf24d5d2e648316468fd4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222127%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGreenspan%20became%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%20during%20Ronald%20Reagan's%20second%20term%20as%20president.%3Cp%3EAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20also%20helped%20to%20modernize%20the%20Fed's%20approach%20to%20dealing%20with%20the%20public.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20Fed%20did%20not%20make%20public%20statements%20about%20what%20its%20target%20interest%20rate%20was%20or%20how%20it%20viewed%20the%20economy.%20But%20under%20Greenspan%2C%20the%20Fed%20and%20its%20interest%20rate-setting%20body%2C%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%2C%20began%20to%20publicly%20declare%20its%20monetary%20policy%20decisions%20and%20release%20the%20minutes%20of%20its%20meetings.%20Greenspan%20also%20elevated%20the%20public%20profile%20of%20the%20Chairman's%20job%2C%20leading%20media%20outlets%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F11%2F02%2Fbooks%2Freview%2Falan-greenspan-capitalism-in-america-adrian-wooldridge.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edub%20him%20a%20%26quot%3Brock%20star%26quot%3B%20economist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20that%20Greenspan%20helped%20bring%20more%20information%20about%20the%20Fed%20to%20the%20public%2C%20he%20also%20perfected%20an%20inscrutable%2C%20academic%20way%20of%20speaking%20dubbed%20%26quot%3BFedspeak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20I've%20become%20a%20central%20banker%2C%20I've%20learned%20to%20mumble%20with%20great%20incoherence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20once%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20seem%20unduly%20clear%20to%20you%2C%20you%20must%20have%20misunderstood%20what%20I%20said.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20using%20language%20that%20inspired%20Wall%20Street%20to%20create%20a%20cottage%20industry%20of%20professional%20Fed%20translators%2C%20Greenspan%20was%20occasionally%20able%20to%20introduce%20big%2C%20clear%20ideas%20about%20the%20economy.%20The%20most%20famous%20of%20these%20was%20his%20December%201996%20speech%20musing%20on%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20Fed%20could%20use%20monetary%20policy%20to%20counter%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20the%20stock%20market's%20%26quot%3Birrational%20exuberance.%26quot%3B%20The%20comment%20was%20widely%20understood%20as%20Greenspan%20warning%20that%20stock%20prices%20may%20have%20been%20too%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20speech%20caused%20some%20heartburn%20at%20the%20time%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20little%20over%20three%20years%20before%20Greenspan's%20worries%20about%20high%20asset%20values%20would%20come%20to%20fruition%20with%20the%20dot-com%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ee86118-ac80-4f14-a558-91f3dd63a69c%5C%22%3EA%20complicated%20legacy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20relatively%20strong%20economy%20that%20Greenspan%20presided%20over%20during%20his%20chairmanship%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-greenspans-slow-downward-spiral-2010-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMaestro%20was%20not%20without%20critics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20accused%20the%20economist%20of%20being%20outwardly%20partisan%2C%20supporting%20George%20W.%20Bush's%20tax%20cut%20and%20Social%20Security%20privatization%20plans.%20Support%20for%20the%20plans%20drew%20criticism%20from%20liberal%20economists%20like%20Paul%20Krugman%2C%20who%20in%202005%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2005%2F02%2F18%2Fopinion%2Fthreecard-maestro.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20then-Chairman%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20another%20partisan%20hack%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Democratic%20politicians%20like%20Senate%20Minority%20Leader%20Harry%20Reid%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F08%2F04%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Freid-has-long-history-of-romney-bashing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20similarly%20in%202005%20called%20Greenspan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20biggest%20political%20hacks%20we%20have%20in%20Washington.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20more%20controversial%20still%20was%20Greenspan's%20supposed%20role%20in%20creating%20the%20housing%20bubble%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2013%2Foct%2F28%2Falan-greenspan-housing-market-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECritics%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Greenspan's%20decisions%20to%20keep%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%20low%20following%20the%20dot-com%20crash%20(the%20effective%20Fed%20funds%20rate%20remained%20below%202%25%20from%20December%202001%20through%20November%202004)%2C%20distaste%20for%20regulations%2C%20and%20apparent%20support%20for%20the%20complex%20mortgage%20products%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20bubble's%20inflation%20all%20contributed%20to%20the%20worst%20recession%20since%20the%20Great%20Depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%202008%20congressional%20testimony%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2008%2F10%2F24%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2F24panel.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenspan%20admitted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20his%20distaste%20for%20regulation%20may%20have%20been%20problematic%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20housing%20crisis%2C%20but%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2Fid%2F24016186%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomist%20vehemently%20denied%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20his%20low-interest-rate%20policies%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20decade%20contributed%20substantially%20to%20the%20bubble.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F81c05200-03f2-11dd-b28b-000077b07658%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHe%20argued%20in%20an%20April%202008%20op-ed%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bthe%20evidence%20of%20monetary%20policy%20adding%20to%20the%20bubble%20is%20statistically%20very%20fragile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff01efe1-24ff-4cab-ac62-c6319efa771b%5C%22%3EStepping%20down%20and%20looking%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20tenure%20as%20Chairman%2C%20Greenspan%20returned%20to%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20founding%20the%20economics%20consultancy%20Greenspan%20Associates.%20Greenspan%20was%20hired%20to%20advise%20a%20slew%20of%20financial%20institutions%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2007%2F08%2F13%2Fformer-fed-chief-greenspan-to-advise-deutsche-bank.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeutsche%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-2007-may-17-fi-pimco17-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPacific%20Investment%20Management%20Company%2C%20or%20PIMCO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20also%20regularly%20commented%20on%20economic%20affairs%20and%20published%20a%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3D3603fb8ed0964e35a9e858e3804fc21fd1a3a5ba831768270c1c0086e5767143%26postID%3D6a391d63f9367a0a3d0e666a%26postSlug%3Dalan-greenspan-dead-100-former-federal-reserve-chair-2026-6%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FAge-Turbulence-Adventures-New-World%252Fdp%252F0143114166%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAge%20of%20Turbulence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20soon%20after%20leaving%20the%20Fed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspan%20is%20survived%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1997%2F04%2F06%2Fstyle%2Falan-greenspan-andrea-mitchell.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20second%20wife%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20journalist%20Andrea%20Mitchell.%20The%20pair's%20first%20date%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farchive.boston.com%2Fae%2Fbooks%2Farticles%2F2007%2F09%2F20%2Finsight_humility_fill_greenspans_world%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenspan%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20mostly%20spent%20discussing%20monopolies%2C%20and%20he%20invited%20Mitchell%20back%20to%20his%20apartment%20to%20read%20the%20essay%20he%20had%20written%20on%20the%20subject.%20They%20eventually%20married%20in%201997%20in%20a%20ceremony%20officiated%20by%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsburg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-greenspan-dead-100-former-federal-reserve-chair-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782128601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a391de1f4bed3c6152cc81a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-greenspan-dead-100-former-federal-reserve-chair-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Greenspan%20helped%20make%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%20a%20more%20publicly%20recognizable%20figure%20during%20his%2019%20years%20as%20the%20US'%20top%20central%20banker.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bbryan%40businessinsider.com%20(Bob%20Bryan%2CWill%20Martin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A100%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Put%20Myself%20Forward'%3A%20Andy%20Burnham%20Says%20He%20Will%20Run%20For%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Former%20health%20secretary%20Wes%20Streeting%2C%20who%20previously%20said%20he%20would%20join%20a%