ted%20a%20podcast%20while%20working%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20podcast%20helped%20her%20build%20relationships%20with%20founders%2C%20executives%2C%20and%20tech%20leaders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20left%20Google%20in%20May%20to%20pursue%20an%20AI%20startup%20because%20staying%20felt%20scarier%20than%20leaving.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Aashna%20Doshi%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20former%20Google%20software%20engineer%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20a%20big%20risk%20to%20get%20my%20Google%20job.%20Now%20I'm%20taking%20another%20one%20by%20leaving%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20February%202024%2C%20months%20before%20graduating%20from%20Georgia%20Tech%2C%20I%20received%20a%20full-time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-landed-job-within-90-days-of-aws-layoff-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20offer%20from%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20one%20problem%3A%20The%20offer%20was%20for%20an%20engineering%20role%20based%20in%20California%2C%20and%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20work%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20had%20become%20more%20challenging%20for%20many%20of%20my%20peers%2C%20no%20opportunity%20could%20be%20ignored.%20Even%20so%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20place%20my%20bets%20and%20turn%20the%20offer%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20paid%20off.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20I%20accepted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-tools-software-engineering-jobs-future-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineering%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Google%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20realize%20I'd%20take%20an%20even%20bigger%20risk%20when%20a%20side%20project%20I%20started%20around%20the%20same%20time%20would%20eventually%20push%20me%20to%20leave%20Google%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223a1e9e19-16e4-4b69-9427-bbb90b0bde7a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20something%20creative%20outside%20of%20coding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20I%20really%20enjoyed%20my%20experience%20at%20Google.%20I%20was%20learning%20every%20day%20and%20meeting%20a%20lot%20of%20smart%20people%20from%20diverse%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-lessons-for-leveling-up-in-tech-communication-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20heavily%20technical%20job%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20something%20more%20interactive%20and%20creative%20outside%20of%20sitting%20at%20my%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20meeting%20people%2C%20hearing%20their%20stories%2C%20and%20learning%20from%20them%2C%20which%20eventually%20sparked%20the%20idea%20of%20starting%20a%20podcast.%20In%20early%202025%2C%20while%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-landed-full-time-job-google-19-without-degree-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20at%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20started%20the%20%26quot%3B0%20to%201%26quot%3B%20podcast%20with%20my%20cohost%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20in%20Big%20Tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20name%20for%20the%20show%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20being%20a%20nod%20to%20our%20backgrounds%20in%20software%20engineering%2C%20came%20from%20the%20idea%20that%20there's%20so%20much%20value%20between%20zero%20%E2%80%94%20where%20someone%20started%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20%E2%80%94%20who%20they%20are%20today.%20My%20cohost%20and%20I%20believe%20that%20a%20lot%20can%20be%20learned%20from%20people's%20journeys%2C%20and%20that%20there's%20sometimes%20too%20much%20focus%20on%20where%20people%20are%20rather%20than%20how%20they%20got%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20to%20start%20the%20podcast%20because%20we%20wanted%20a%20creative%20outlet%20outside%20of%20engineering%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20to%20expand%20our%20networks%20and%20connect%20with%20people%20in%20roles%20much%20more%20senior%20than%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22601b4c95-19b1-49c0-a852-15f43a8c5a3f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20podcast%20helped%20us%20%26quot%3Bnetwork%20up%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20early%20guests%20came%20through%20cold%20DMs%2C%20our%20network%2C%20and%20people%20we%20were%20close%20with.%20We%20interviewed%20founders%2C%20engineers%2C%20executives%2C%20and%20creators%20about%20the%20journey%20from%20where%20they%20started%20to%20who%20they%20are%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20picked%20up%20much%20faster%20than%20we%20expected.%20Within%20the%20first%20year%2C%20the%20podcast%20crossed%20100%2C000%20YouTube%20views.%20Eventually%2C%20it%20became%20easier%20to%20reach%20people%2C%20and%20we%20were%20able%20to%20bring%20on%20leaders%20from%20large%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-amazon-microsoft-millennial-tech-job-market-artificial-intelligence-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%20and%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20podcast%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20imagine%20how%20we%20might%20go%20about%20connecting%20with%20someone%20high%20up%20in%20a%20big%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278ec166f-275e-4513-af77-f43c66f89207%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20felt%20like%20the%20right%20time%20to%20leave%20Google%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-earnings-winners-losers-ai-capex-cloud-meta-goog-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you're%20one%20piece%20of%20a%20very%20large%20machine%2C%20and%20I%20craved%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%2C%20move%20fast%2C%20and%20see%20the%20direct%20results%20of%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20AI%20tools%20available%20to%20builders%20right%20now%20are%20unlike%20anything%20we've%20had%20before.%20I%20had%20a%20strong%20conviction%20around%20a%20specific%20idea%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20look%20back%20and%20wish%20I%20had%20taken%20the%20shot%20when%20the%20timing%20was%20this%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-google-adopt-ai-engineer-productivity-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleft%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20go%20all-in%20on%20building%20my%20AI%20startup%2C%20Bounty%2C%20with%20my%20podcast%20co-host.%20It's%20an%20outcome-based%20AI%20marketplace%20where%20companies%20can%20post%20specific%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20like%20sourcing%20candidates%2C%20running%20outreach%2C%20or%20generating%20leads%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%20pay%20for%20verified%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20the%20podcast%20helped%20give%20me%20the%20confidence%20to%20make%20the%20leap.%20We're%20living%20in%20a%20world%20where%20media%20and%20distribution%20are%20everything%20for%20a%20startup%2C%20and%20having%20a%20podcast%20with%20a%20built-in%20audience%20of%20founders%20and%20operators%20%E2%80%94%20the%20exact%20people%20our%20business%20is%20being%20built%20for%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20perfect%20distribution%20channel%20for%20what%20we're%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2259ceaed7-486c-4875-839f-98d2118242fd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20Google%20was%20a%20financial%20risk%20I'm%20willing%20to%20take%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20leaving%20Google%20made%20sense%20from%20a%20personal%20and%20business%20perspective%2C%20giving%20up%20my%20Google%20paycheck%20wasn't%20an%20easy%20decision.%20We're%20still%20pre-launch%20and%20not%20generating%20revenue%20yet.%20I'm%20taking%20a%20founder%20salary%2C%20but%20it's%20definitely%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20I%20was%20making%20at%20Google.%20The%20podcast%20isn't%20generating%20any%20income%20yet%2C%20but%20we're%20hopeful%20it%20will%20soon%20through%20sponsorships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeaving%20Google%20was%20a%20risk%2C%20but%20I've%20always%20believed%20that%20if%20you%20feel%20a%20strong%20enough%20pull%20toward%20something%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20good%20in%20pursuit%20of%20something%20that%20could%20be%20great.%20Financial%20security%20is%20comfortable%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20be%20a%20trap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scarier%20version%20of%20this%20decision%20wasn't%20leaving%20Google.%20It%20was%20staying%20and%20always%20wondering%20what%20could%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20how%20you're%20navigating%20a%20career%20crossroads%3F%20If%20so%2C%20please%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%