the%20retail%20private%20credit%20boom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224917%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Businessmen%20shaking%20hands%20in%20corridor%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a345d27c7a58f814f0d454c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223553%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Edwards%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPrivate%20credit's%20retail%20boom%20was%20enabled%20by%20a%20rule%20change%20that%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20sell%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20Insider%20identified%20at%20least%20%24796%20million%20in%20fees%20for%20advisors%20to%20sell%20these%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20fees%20can%20lead%20to%20large%20differences%20in%20the%20performance%20of%20share%20classes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-fabulous-life-of-boaz-weinstein-2012-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBoaz%20Weinstein%20thinks%20%3C%2Fa%3Eretail%20investors%20who%20have%20plowed%20into%20private%20credit%20and%20regretted%20it%20should%20ask%20their%20wealth%20advisors%20a%20simple%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20were%20you%20paid%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20activist%20investor%2C%20who%20has%20targeted%20Blue%20Owl's%20funds%2C%20argued%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DcRt9ehlFLGo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%20appearance%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20advisors%20were%20rewarded%20with%20lucrative%20commissions%20for%20steering%20clients%20into%20semi-liquid%20retail%20private-credit%20funds.%20A%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20found%20that%20advisors%20have%20collected%20at%20least%20%24796%20million%20selling%20those%20products%20since%202020%20%E2%80%94%20a%20windfall%20made%20possible%20by%20an%20obscure%20SEC%20exemption%20that%20quietly%20reshaped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-blue-owl-institutional-investors-redemptions-bdc-funding-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20private%20credit%20is%20distributed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20wealthy%20individual%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20incentives%20have%20helped%20lay%20the%20tracks%20for%20the%20%2480%20billion%20in%20retail%20private%20credit%20cash%20raised%20through%20business%20development%20companies%2C%20a%20type%20of%20investment%20fund%20that%20makes%20direct%20loans%20to%20small%20and%20midsize%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20entry%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-hot-investment-private-credit-retirement-savings-401k-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprivate%20assets%20into%20retirement%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20driven%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-private-equity-retirement-plan-risk-401k-retail-investor-warning-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-troubles-retirement-funds-401k-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epending%20agency%20rule%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20charge%20different%20fees%20for%20different%20clients%20and%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20sell%20to%20affluent%20individual%20investors%20came%20about%20because%20the%20SEC%20accepted%20a%20five-year-old%20application%20for%20an%20exemption%20to%20Investment%20Act%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20commission%20costs%20are%20not%20reported%20to%20regulators%2C%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20indicates%20that%20the%20total%20number%20could%20be%20well%20over%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDhruv%20Maniktala%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20multi-family%20office%20True%20North%20Advisors%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20promised%20yields%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-institutional-investors-are-putting-their-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprivate%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20the%20primary%20driver%20for%20retail%20demand%2C%20just%20as%20they%20were%20for%20institutional%20investors.%20However%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20explosion%20in%20growth%20has%20been%20helped%20by%20the%20brokers%20who%20had%20a%20large%20incentive%20share%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20absolutely%20true%20that%20the%20structure%20of%20these%20funds%20have%20been%20developed%20so%20as%20to%20incentivize%20the%20broker-dealers%20to%20sell%20more%20and%20more%20and%20more%20of%20these%2C%26quot%3B%20Maniktala%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20wave%20of%20redemptions%20in%20BDCs%20has%20prompted%20some%20critics%2C%20like%20Weinstein%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Bloomberg%2C%20to%20wonder%20whether%20retail%20investors%20really%20understood%20the%20trade-offs%20they%20were%20making%20between%20performance%20and%20liquidity.%20(Weinstein%20declined%20an%20interview%20for%20this%20story.)%20The%20industry%20has%20pushed%20back%20against%20this%20narrative%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-institutional-investors-are-putting-their-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlackstone%20president%20Jon%20Gray%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20liquidity%20constraints%20are%20repeatedly%20mentioned%20in%20the%20firm's%20marketing%20materials%20on%20its%20recent%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-20-billion-redemption-data-blue-owl-blackstone-apollo-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eredemptions%20are%20likely%20to%20continue%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20Blackstone's%20flagship%20private%20credit%20fund%2C%20BCRED%2C%20announced%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20investors%20asked%20to%20redeem%2010%25%20of%20shares%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20%E2%80%94%20and%20questions%20of%20what%20is%20causing%20investors%20to%20pull%20their%20cash%2C%20and%20put%20it%20there%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20swirl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20a%20niche%20administrative%20change%20in%20securities%20regulations%20helped%20to%20kick-start%20private%20credit's%20retail%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f897c8b9-0c2a-4b43-8af8-0de2911d1b9c%5C%22%3EHow%20share%20class%20changes%20opened%20the%20gates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrivately%20traded%20BDCs%2C%20offered%20by%20wealth%20advisors%20rather%20than%20available%20on%20public%20markets%2C%20remained%20out%20of%20the%20public%20eye%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20holding%20them%20back%20was%20the%20inability%20to%20offer%20multiple%20share%20classes%2C%20according%20to%20a%202020%20memo%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eversheds-sutherland.com%2Fen%2Funited-states%2Finsights%2Fsec-grants-multi-class-exemptive-order-to-a-bdc-for-the-first-time%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%20firm%20Eversheds%20Sutherland%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Offering%20different%20share%20classes%2C%20with%20different%20fees%20or%20commission%20structures%2C%20%26quot%3Bfacilitates%20the%20distribution%20of%20shares.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20if%20financial%20advisors%20don't%20get%20paid%20a%20commission%20to%20sell%20something%2C%20they%20are%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20pitch%20it%20to%20their%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202014%2C%20global%20asset%20manager%20Future%20Standard%20aimed%20to%20change%20this%20for%20its%20FS%20Energy%20and%20Power%20Fund.%20The%20firm%20applied%20for%20an%20SEC%20%26quot%3Bexemptive%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20that%20BDCs%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20use%20multiple%20share%20classes%2C%20as%20mutual%20funds%20have%20since%201995%2C%20to%20target%20different%20investor%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SEC%20did%20not%20move%20quickly.%20The%20application%20took%20over%20five%20years%20and%20underwent%20four%20separate%20amendments%20before%20the%20SEC%20signaled%20its%20approval%20in%20January%202020%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20official%20green%20light%20in%20February%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Future%20Standard's%20application%20opened%20the%20door%2C%20others%20quickly%20followed.%20In%20February%202020%2C%20BCRED%2C%20now%20the%20industry's%20largest%20with%20%2445%20billion%20in%20net%20assets%2C%20filed%20its%20first%20draft%20registration%20statement%20with%20the%20SEC%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20may%20submit%20its%20own%20application%20for%20an%20exemptive%20order.%20By%20April%202020%2C%20it%20was%20already%20planning%20to%20offer%20different%20share%20classes%2C%20and%20its%20application%20was%20accepted%20in%20October%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-owl-private-credit-firm-redemptions-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlue%20Owl%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20still%20Owl%20Rock%2C%20had%20its%20own%20application%20accepted%20a%20month%20earlier.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackstone-private-credit-warning-signs-financial-crisis-risks-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAres%2C%20Apollo%2C%20BlackRock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20others%20began%20launching%20their%20own%20private%20credit%20BDCs%20for%20retail%20investors%2C%20they%20also%20applied%20for%20this%20exemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202013%20through%202020%2C%20non-traded%20and%20private%20BDCs%20raised%20%2435%20billion.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20same%20asset%20class%20has%20raised%20%24152%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.hl.com%2Fpdf%2F2026%2Fbdc-monitor-spring-2026-.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHoulihan%20Lokey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20same%20time%20period%2C%20BDCs%20grew%20from%20a%20%2421.5%20billion%20fair-value%20portfolio%20to%20a%20%24393.6%20billion%20fair-value%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a4a13b3-d34b-4e7d-86aa-6f66aba8c0c9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20fees%20change%20behavior%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOffering%20multiple%20share%20classes%20helped%20private-credit%20firms%20fit%20neatly%20into%20the%20wealth-management%20ecosystem%2C%20said%20Maniktala.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20different%20classes%20are%20designed%20for%20different%20types%20of%20advisors.%20Class%20I%20shares%2C%20which%20carry%20no%20sales%20commissions%20or%20servicing%20fees%2C%20are%20typically%20sold%20to%20institutional%20investors%20and%20fee-only%20registered%20investment%20advisors%2C%20who%2C%20instead%20of%20receiving%20a%20cut%20for%20selling%20an%20asset%2C%20charge%20clients%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20total%20assets.%20Other%20classes%2C%20such%20as%20Class%20S%20and%20Class%20D%20shares%2C%20can%20be%20sold%20by%20advisors%20and%20broker-dealers%20who%20can%20receive%20commissions%20for%20selling%20the%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20major%20non-traded%20BDCs%20offering%20multiple%20share%20classes%2C%20roughly%2071%25%20of%20outstanding%20shares%20are%20Class%20I%20shares%20that%20carry%20neither%20sales%20commissions%20nor%20servicing%20fees%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis.%20At%20BCRED%2C%20Class%20I%20shares%20account%20for%2068%25%20of%20outstanding%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20two%20types%20of%20fees%20that%20are%20typically%20charged%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ctable%3E%3Ccolgroup%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20Class%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3ETypical%20Buyer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EUpfront%20Commission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnnual%20Servicing%20Fee%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClass%20I%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EInstitutions%2C%20fee-only%20RIAs%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3ENone%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3ENone%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClass%20D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EBroker-dealers%2C%20commission-based%20advisors%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EUp%20to%201.5%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E0.25%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClass%20S%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EBroker-dealers%2C%20commission-based%20advisors%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EUp%20to%203.5%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E0.85%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20incentives%20can%20be%20powerful%20for%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffee-only-versus-fee-based-financial-advisors-2014-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaid%20on%20commission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wealth-industry%20veterans%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20has%20always%20been%20ample%20incentive%20pointing%20the%20advisor%20right%20to%20the%20fees%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Charles%20Urquhart%2C%20founder%20of%20advisor%20education%20and%20consulting%20firm%20Fixed%20Income%20Resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdvisors%20used%20to%20work%20from%20sales%20offering%20sheets%20that%20listed%20the%20sales%20commission%20on%20the%20right-hand%20side%20of%20the%20page%2C%26quot%3B%20Urquhart%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20larger%20the%20commission%2C%20the%20more%20an%20advisor's%20eye%20went%20there%20first.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20March%202020%2C%20those%20commission-bearing%20share%20classes%20have%20generated%20at%20least%20%24796%20million%20for%20advisors%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20industry%20insider%20disputed%20that%20commissions%20drove%20demand%2C%20arguing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fees%20have%20put%20the%20asset%20class%20on%20par%20and%20helped%20it%20compete%20with%20other%20asset%20classes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20person%20said%20that%20in%20fee-based%20accounts%2C%20a%20client%20who%20invests%20in%20one%20of%20these%20BDCs%20would%20be%20paying%20distribution%20fees%20%26quot%3Bin%20line%20with%20the%20norms%26quot%3B%20for%20other%20assets%20like%20stocks%2C%20bonds%2C%20and%20ETFs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e318f607-4ad5-4ccc-9938-75cbcd6c9172%5C%22%3EA%20breakdown%20of%20fees%20paid%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20Blue%20Owl%20disclosed%20the%20size%20of%20upfront%20commissions%20paid%2C%20reporting%20%2467.6%20million%20in%20upfront%20commissions%20across%20its%20two%20non-traded%20BDCs%20since%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20firms%20do%20not%20disclose%20those%20figures%2C%20and%20commissions%20paid%20by%20others%20could%20be%20higher%20or%20lower.%20Applying%20Blue%20Owl's%20ratio%20of%20commissions%20to%20net%20assets%20to%20the%20more%20than%20%24106%20billion%20held%20across%20the%20industry's%20largest%20retail%20private-credit%20BDCs%20that%20charge%20fees%20to%20more%20than%201%25%20of%20clients%2C%20Business%20Insider%20estimates%20advisors%20may%20have%20collected%20over%20%24315%20million%20in%20upfront%20commissions%2C%20following%20the%20enforcement%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackstone's%20BCRED%20has%20paid%20out%20%24354%20million%20through%20annual%20servicing%20fees%20since%202021%2C%20while%20Blue%20Owl%20has%20paid%20%24138%20million%20across%20its%20two%20BDCs.%20Business%20Insider%20identified%20%24711%20million%20in%20servicing%20and%20distribution%20fees%20paid%20to%20advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Blackstone%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20fees%20but%20said%20that%20its%20%26quot%3Btrue%20north%20remains%20delivering%20superior%20net%20returns%20to%20our%20end%20investors%2C%20and%20that%20is%20exactly%20what%20we've%20done.%26quot%3B%20They%20pointed%20to%20BCRED's%20Class%20I%20shares%209.3%25%20annualized%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20over%2050%25%20premium%20to%20leveraged%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20firms%20mentioned%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20or%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFee-bearing%20classes%20can%20materially%20affect%20investor%20returns.%20Since%20inception%2C%20Class%20I%20shares%20of%20Blue%20Owl%20Credit%20Income%20Corp%20have%20returned%209.17%25%20annually%2C%20compared%20with%207.51%25%20for%20Class%20S%20shares%20purchased%20with%20the%20maximum%20sales%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20investor%20who%20put%20%24100%2C000%20into%20the%20fund%20in%20March%202021%20through%20Class%20I%20shares%20would%20have%20earned%20roughly%20%2416%2C300%20more%20than%20an%20investor%20who%20purchased%20Class%20S%20shares.%20More%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20Class%20I%20investors'%20gains%20over%20that%20period%20were%20effectively%20redirected%20to%20compensate%20the%20broker%20who%20sold%20the%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail-private-credit-boom-advisor-fees-2020-rule-change-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782122101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a345d38f4bed3c6152cbedd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail-private-credit-boom-advisor-fees-2020-rule-change-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20regulatory%20move%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20private%20credit%20retail%20funds%20to%20offer%20different%20shares%20and%20for%20advisors%20to%20collect%20%24796%20million%20in%20fees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22anicoll%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Nicoll)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22c