%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFedWatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20here's%20where%20things%20stand%20now%20after%20some%20major%20shifting%20(as%20of%20Sunday%20evening)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EJuly%20meeting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E39%25%20chance%20of%20hike%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeptember%20meeting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E74%25%20chance%20of%20hike%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOctober%20meeting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E78%25%20chance%20of%20hike%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecember%20meeting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E90%25%20chance%20of%20hike%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20sticking%20point%20%E2%80%94%20as%20it%20usually%20is%20with%20the%20Fed%20%E2%80%94%20is%20inflation.%20While%20recent%20data%20hasn't%20come%20in%20hotter%20than%20forecasts%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20consumer%20prices%20are%20still%20rising%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20in%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDo80v%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20of%20the%20year-over-year%20percent%20change%20in%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDo80v%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWe'll%20get%20the%20next%20major%20input%20this%20Thursday%3A%20the%20May%20personal%20consumption%20expenditure%20(PCE)%20index%2C%20which%20is%20generally%20viewed%20as%20the%20Fed's%20preferred%20inflation%20gauge.%20June%20CPI%20isn't%20due%20until%20July%2014%2C%20so%20we%20have%20a%20while%20to%20marinate%20with%20the%20current%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20timing%20still%20uncertain%2C%20we%20can%20at%20least%20examine%20the%20arguments%20for%20and%20against%20rate%20hikes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArguments%20in%20favor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInflation%20isn't%20behaving.%20The%20Fed's%20mandate%20is%20technically%202%25.%20We're%20at%204.2%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20labor%20market%20is%20too%20resilient%20to%20need%20more%20monetary%20support.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETariff%20risks%20are%20still%20working%20their%20way%20through%20the%20system.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArguments%20against%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInflation%20is%20elevated%2C%20but%20not%20accelerating.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEconomic%20growth%20is%20already%20slowing%20(i.e.%20consumer%20spending%2C%20manufacturing%20activity).%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETariff%20inflation%20is%20largely%20a%20supply%20shock%2C%20and%20doesn't%20necessarily%20reflect%20excessive%20demand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-fed-rate-hike-timing-kevin-warsh-monetary-policy-outlook-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782121801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3841a4c7a58f814f0d4ce7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-fed-rate-hike-timing-kevin-warsh-monetary-policy-outlook-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kevin%20Warsh%20is%20proving%20hard%20to%20read%20so%20far.%20With%20data%20sparse%20for%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%2C%20traders%20have%20their%20work%20cut%20out.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jciolli%40businessinsider.com%20(Joe%20Ciolli)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mike%20Leigh%20Collection%20Launched%20by%20Salaud%20Morisset%20With%20Studiocanal%2C%20BFI%2C%20Film4%3B%20Titles%20Include%20%E2%80%98Life%20Is%20Sweet%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Topsy-Turvy%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Vera%20Drake%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782121781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2