ult%20to%20be%20the%20mom%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20while%20navigating%20her%20divorce.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amber%20Campbell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20studied%20child%20development%20partly%20to%20give%20my%20future%20children%20what%20I%20didn't%20have%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThen%20my%20marriage%20imploded%2C%20and%20the%20stress%20of%20a%20high-conflict%20divorce%20made%20me%20unrecognizable.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20daughters%20are%20grown%20now%2C%20and%20I'm%20trying%20to%20be%20the%20mom%20they%20deserve.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20my%20daughters%20and%20I%20canvassed%20the%20neighborhood%20trick-or-treating%2C%20my%208-year-old%20dressed%20as%20a%20devil%20and%20her%205-year-old%20sister%20as%20a%20superhero%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-one-habit-transformed-my-motherhood-and-sanity-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20frustration%20was%20growing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20youngest%20was%20refusing%20to%20say%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%26quot%3B%20as%20neighbors%20dropped%20handfuls%20of%20candy%20into%20her%20bucket%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20embarrassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSay%20'thank%20you%2C'%20or%20Halloween%20is%20cancelled%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20stared%20at%20me%20stubbornly%20while%20her%20sister's%20face%20dropped%2C%20and%20I%20instantly%20realized%20my%20mistake.%20I%20was%20engaging%20in%20a%20power%20struggle%20with%20a%20kindergartner%20%E2%80%94%20exactly%20the%20opposite%20of%20what%20I%20learned%20in%20college%2C%20where%20I%20took%20multiple%20early%20childhood%20education%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20my%20way%20through%20school%20as%20a%20nanny%20and%20preschool%20teacher%2C%20aiming%20to%20counteract%20my%20own%20tumultuous%20childhood%20by%20learning%20age-appropriate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudy-self-regulation-parenting-still-tests-my-skills-patience-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epositive%20parenting%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20me%20give%20my%20future%20children%20the%20childhood%20they%20deserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20life%20took%20unexpected%20turns%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20always%20handle%20them%20well.%20Today%2C%20looking%20back%2C%20I%20deeply%20regret%20the%20mother%20I%20temporarily%20became%20during%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-and-life-avoiding-burnout-during-divorce-attorney-advice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estressful%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ce36efa-0945-4db3-94bc-531163b3c467%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20divorce%20changed%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20just%20five%20years%2C%20my%20marriage%20imploded%2C%20and%20custody%20became%20a%20question%2C%20not%20a%20given.%20I%20spent%20the%20next%20several%20years%20terrified%20that%20I%20would%20lose%20my%20children%2C%20making%20me%20anxious%2C%20depressed%2C%20and%20dysregulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20expected%20to%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhave-to-let-go-of-perfectionism-be-good-parent-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eperfect%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20after%20working%20hard%20to%20give%20my%20daughters%20a%20better%20childhood%20than%20mine%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225312%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20children%20are%20shown%20in%20silhouette%20while%20standing%20on%20a%20fence%20in%20front%20of%20water.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3449d9f4bed3c6152cbd8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222988%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20she%20worked%20hard%20to%20give%20her%20children%20a%20better%20childhood%20than%20she%20had.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amber%20Campbell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20physically%20present%20but%20mentally%20calculating%20bills%2C%20rehearsing%20court%20testimony%2C%20or%20wondering%20how%20I%20would%20pay%20next%20month's%20rent.%20Even%20when%20we%20were%20at%20the%20playground%20or%20curled%20up%20reading%20books%20together%2C%20part%20of%20me%20was%20usually%20somewhere%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221abd36ff-148a-473b-8848-629052b93c72%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20terrified%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20yelled%20too%20much%20during%20these%20years%2C%20too.%20Once%2C%20while%20on%20a%20rare-for-us%20vacation%2C%20I%20let%20my%20frustration%20get%20the%20best%20of%20me%20and%20snapped%20at%20one%20of%20my%20daughters%20when%20she%20was%20just%20being%20silly.%20I%20feel%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fstress-relief%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20was%20holding%20on%20to%20ruined%20our%20vacation%20when%20my%20kids%20were%208%20and%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20we%20still%20shared%20many%20happy%20memories%20over%20the%20years%20%E2%80%94%20sledding%20in%20the%20winter%2C%20and%20enjoying%20picnic%20dinners%20by%20the%20lake%20on%20long%20summer%20days.%20But%20certain%20images%20from%20those%20years%20still%20sting%2C%20and%20I%20know%20things%20would%20have%20been%20different%20had%20I%20not%20been%20stuck%20in%20survival%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20I%20cringed%20in%20shame%2C%20remembering%20the%20night%20I%20fell%20asleep%20before%20exchanging%20the%20tooth%20under%20my%20oldest%20daughter's%20pillow%20with%20a%20note%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftooth-fairy-how-much-per-teeth-inchstones-inflation-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETooth%20Fairy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Or%20the%20time%20I%20ranted%20about%20something%20so%20insignificant%20I%20don't%20even%20remember%20it%20now%2C%20and%20she%20said%20quietly%2C%20%26quot%3BMom%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20get%20so%20mad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20lay%20in%20bed%20that%20night%2C%20I%20couldn't%20sleep%20as%20her%20words%20ran%20through%20my%20mind%20on%20a%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20what%20good%20parenting%20looked%20like.%20I%20just%20couldn't%20always%20access%20that%20version%20of%20myself.%20My%20girls%20deserved%20a%20mom%20who%20wasn't%20constantly%20afraid%2C%20and%20I%20deserved%20a%20life%20that%20didn't%20require%20me%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22efcb34c2-8cdb-432c-aa27-dfaeeb018d43%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20am%20choosing%20to%20live%20differently%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20always%20regret%20how%20much%20of%20my%20fear%20and%20stress%20they%20absorbed%20during%20those%20years.%20But%20I%20also%20remind%20myself%20that%20it's%20never%20too%20late%20to%20be%20the%20mom%20I%20always%20dreamed%20of%20%E2%80%94%20calm%2C%20present%2C%20supportive%2C%20and%20someone%20whose%20emotions%20my%20daughters%20don't%20feel%20responsible%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20grieve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-want-to-show-my-son-i-can-be-happy-single-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20could've%20had%20even%20as%20I've%20watched%20them%20grow%20into%20smart%2C%20capable%2C%20and%20kind%20young%20women%20who%20I%20couldn't%20be%20more%20proud%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20change%20who%20I%20was%20then%2C%20but%20I%20can%20choose%20who%20I%20am%20now.%20I%20constantly%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20make%20it%20up%20to%20them%2C%20knowing%20that%20every%20visit%2C%20phone%20call%2C%20and%20conversation%20is%20another%20opportunity%20to%20show%20up%20differently%20than%20I%20once%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20when%20my%20oldest%20daughter%20called%20recently%20and%20I%20told%20her%20I%20wasn't%20busy%20even%20though%20I%20only%20had%20five%20minutes%20before%20I%20needed%20to%20rinse%20the%20color%20out%20of%20my%20hair.%20She%20immediately%20launched%20into%20a%20long%2C%20heartfelt%20story%20that%20I%20wasn't%20about%20to%