oods%20the%20market%20with%20more%20content%20than%20ever%2C%20marketers%20will%20need%20to%20be%20more%20creative.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERaja%20Rajamannar%2C%20Mastercard's%20former%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%2C%20spent%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20overseeing%20marketing%20for%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20recognizable%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20tenure%20as%20CMCO%20from%202013%20to%20the%20start%20of%202026%2C%20he%20made%20a%20decision%20that%20many%20marketers%20would%20consider%20unthinkable%3A%20He%20permanently%20cut%20Mastercard's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-influencer-ad-spend-37-billion-marketing-growth-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadvertising%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%2070%25%20as%20part%20of%20a%20progressive%20shift%20during%20Mastercard's%20marketing%20transformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20didn't%20hurt%20the%20business%2C%20Rajamannar%20said.%20Instead%2C%20he%20redirected%20much%20of%20that%20spending%20into%20experiences%2C%20sponsorships%2C%20and%20consumer%20engagement%20programs%20that%20he%20says%20delivered%20stronger%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20upcoming%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Fcmo-insider%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECMO%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20Rajamannar%20says%20that%20traditional%20advertising%20no%20longer%20works%20the%20way%20marketers%20think%20it%20does.%20Consumers%20are%20overwhelmed%2C%20distracted%2C%20and%20increasingly%20determined%20to%20avoid%20ads%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20artificial%20intelligence%20floods%20the%20market%20with%20more%20content%20than%20ever%2C%20he%20argues%20that%20marketers%20will%20need%20to%20rely%20less%20on%20volume%20and%20more%20on%20creativity%20and%20human%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dcc4fc47-84ff-4741-8661-ba24c0cd3331%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsumers%20don't%20want%20more%20ads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERajamannar's%20views%20come%20first%20from%20his%20own%20experience%20as%20a%20consumer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20consumer%20today%2C%20do%20I%20like%20advertisements%3F%20I%20hate%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20an%20interruption%20to%20my%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20streaming%20services%20that%20offer%20consumers%20the%20option%20to%20pay%20more%20to%20avoid%20advertising.%20To%20him%2C%20that%20reflects%20a%20broader%20reality%3A%20Many%20consumers%20would%20rather%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-spend-marketing-data-streaming-tv-netflix-disney-plus-hulu-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espend%20money%20than%20watch%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20consumers%20are%20inundated%20with%20marketing%20messages.%20Rajamannar%20said%20the%20average%20person%20sees%20between%203%2C000%20and%2010%2C000%20ads%20each%20day%2C%20creating%20information%20overload%20that%20causes%20people%20to%20tune%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20cited%20shrinking%20attention%20spans.%20Consumers'%20attention%20spans%20have%20fallen%2C%20he%20says%2C%20leaving%20marketers%20with%20mere%20seconds%20to%20capture%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaken%20together%2C%20he%20said%2C%20those%20trends%20raise%20a%20fundamental%20question%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertising-dead-mastercard-senior-fellow-art-of-marketing-raja-rajamannar-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhether%20advertising%20remains%20the%20most%20effective%3C%2Fa%3E%20way%20to%20communicate%20with%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20need%20to%20communicate%20with%20the%20consumers%20doesn't%20go%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20way%20we%20are%20communicating%20is%20not%20great.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2217a7fd70-af9b-4054-b45d-b132a96361ea%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%20after%20Mastercard%20cut%20spending%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20continue%20investing%20heavily%20in%20traditional%20advertising%2C%20Mastercard%20shifted%20resources%20into%20other%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Rajamannar's%20leadership%2C%20the%20company%20invested%20in%20platforms%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FPriceless.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPriceless.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20strategy%20focused%20on%20creating%20experiences%20that%20consumers%20would%20remember%20and%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20taken%20permanently%2070%25%20of%20our%20advertising%20dollars%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Rajamannar%20said.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20happened%20to%20the%20business%20that%20is%20negative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Mastercard's%20standing%20improved%20during%20that%20period.%20According%20to%20Rajamannar%2C%20the%20brand%20moved%20from%20No.%2087%20to%20No.%2012%20in%20BrandZ's%20ranking%20of%20valuable%20brands%20and%20became%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20brands%20in%20the%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20continued%20to%20compete%20against%20rivals%20with%20larger%20marketing%20budgets%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Rajamannar%2C%20the%20experience%20reinforced%20his%20belief%20that%20many%20companies%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencer-industry-marketing-fraud-discrimination-unethical-deals-content-creators-brands-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espending%20more%20on%20advertising%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdvertising%20dollars%20and%20marketing%20dollars%20today%2C%20they%20are%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20many%20cases%2C%20if%20we%20go%20through%20the%20details%20by%20taking%20them%20down%2C%20nothing%20negative%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20because%2C%20anyway%2C%20you%20are%20not%20investing%20them%20in%20the%20most%20effective%20and%20efficient%20fashion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be732d82-ab61-405c-a262-7101ca8fe3fc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20is%20making%20marketers%20rethink%20their%20role%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmastercard-former-cmo-ai-ushering-golden-era-marketing-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERajamannar%20believes%20artificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20accelerating%20the%20need%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20tools%20can%20generate%20large%20volumes%20of%20marketing%20content%20in%20minutes%2C%20lowering%20barriers%20for%20companies%20of%20all%20sizes.%20But%20he%20argued%20that%20widespread%20access%20to%20the%20same%20tools%20creates%20a%20new%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20is%20the%20small%20companies%20are%20able%20to%20effectively%20now%20compete%20against%20the%20large%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20you%20realize%20it%20becomes%20a%20sea%20of%20sameness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20environment%20makes%20creativity%20and%20consumer%20understanding%20more%20valuable%2C%20not%20less%2C%20he%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERajamannar%20says%20that%20marketers%20must%20become%20more%20fluent%20in%20technology%20and%20business%20results%20while%20continuing%20to%20understand%20human%20behavior.%20He%20adds%20that%20marketers%20often%20lose%20credibility%20when%20they%20focus%20on%20awareness%2C%20reach%2C%20or%20other%20marketing%20metrics%20instead%20of%20business%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20spreads%20across%20the%20industry%2C%20he%20sees%20both%20risk%20and%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20opportunity%20for%20marketers%26quot%3B%20is%20differentiating%20themselves%20through%20innovation%20and%20creativity%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20human-to-human%20connection%20that%20sells%20your%20products%20and%20brands.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraditional-ads-dead-mastercard-senior-fellow-raja-rajamannar-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782120241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32d5ab564c774507cd3a86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraditional-ads-dead-mastercard-senior-fellow-raja-rajamannar-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Mastercard%20CMO%20Raja%20Rajamannar%20says%20consumers%20are%20tuning%20out%20ads%20and%20that%20marketers%20must%20focus%20on%20creativity%2C%20experiences%2C%20and%20human%20connection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jorwig%40businessinsider.com%20(Jessica%20Orwig%2CLeon%20Siciliano%2CLara%20O'Reilly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Julia%20Roberts%20hangs%20out%20with%20Henry%20and%20Hazel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782120070000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131905275%2Cimgsize-121506.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fjulia-roberts-hangs-out-with-son-henry-and-daughter-hazel-in-a-rare-outing%2Farticleshow%2F131905242.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F131905242.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJulia%20Roberts%2C%20the%20celebrated%20Hollywood%20starry-eyed%2C%20made%20a%20rare%20public%20appearance%20alongside%20her%20children%2C%20Henry%2C%20who%20recently%20turned%2019%2C%20and%2021-year-old%20Hazel.%20Accompanied%20by%20her%20stylist%2C%20this%20family%20outing%20reveals%20a%20personal%20side%20of%20the%20actress%2C%20highlighting%20a%20departure%20from%20her%20often%20shielded%20private%20