20New%20Jersey%2C%20when%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fromanticize-your-commute-tiktok-trend-rto-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommutes%20mid-day%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20runs%20an%20early-afternoon%20errand%2C%20only%20to%20find%20the%20sidewalks%20stuffed%20with%20people.%20Then%20comes%20the%20sobering%20realization%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'well%2C%20you're%20also%20not%20at%20work.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-new-yorkers-commute-and-who-commutes-subway-bus-driving-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E3%3A44%20pm%20express%20train%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20catches%20from%20New%20York%20City%20back%20to%20Jersey%20should%20be%20a%20fairly%20breezy%2C%20off-peak%20commute.%20Instead%2C%20she%20often%20finds%20herself%20shoulder%20to%20shoulder%20with%20other%20supposedly%20savvy%20workers.%20Across%20the%20country%2C%20there's%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-side-hustles-commute-uber-etsy-in-person-hybrid-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20influx%20of%20commuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Erika%3A%20Folks%20who%2C%20pre-pandemic%2C%20would%20be%20chained%20to%20their%20desks%20until%205%20p.m.%20(at%20least).%20Now%2C%20these%20workers%20are%20far%20more%20flexible%20%E2%80%94%20able%20to%20head%20home%20a%20little%20early%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-return-to-the-office-commute-childcare-nightmare-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eto%20handle%20childcare%20pickups%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20errands%2C%20or%20pets%2C%20and%20then%20pick%20up%20work%20remotely%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20means%20we're%20all%20commuting%20in%20really%20weird%20ways.%20If%20you've%20decided%20to%20drive%20home%20at%202%3A17%20p.m.%2C%20or%20hop%20on%20the%20subway%20at%2010%3A08%20a.m.%2C%20you've%20probably%20noticed%20you're%20not%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20you%20thought%20you%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hours%20have%20been%2C%20I%20think%2C%20changing%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20jobs.%20They're%20allowing%20people%20to%20come%20in%20either%20later%20or%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richard%20Hack%2C%20a%20med%20tech%20based%20in%20Pennsylvania.%20Hack's%20daily%20commute%20of%20nearly%20160%20miles%20round-trip%20has%20slowly%20expanded%20from%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20to%20around%20two%20hours%20each%20way.%20He%20now%20leaves%20his%20house%20at%205%20a.m.%20to%20make%20a%207%20a.m.%20start%2C%20and%20heads%20out%20at%203%3A30%20p.m%20to%20make%20it%20home%20by%206%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20and%20reshaped%20work%2C%20we%20were%20handed%20something%20beautiful%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpandemic-ended-american-daily-commute-to-work-transit-rush-hour-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20end%20of%20the%20commute%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20as%20employees%20began%20getting%20called%20back%20in%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-job-openings-decline-as-more-companies-return-to-office-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eremote%20work%20dissipated%20for%20many%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20lavish%20travel-less%20era%20quickly%20came%20to%20a%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Traffic%20on%20Interstate%2080%20in%20El%20Cerrito%2C%20California%2C%20US%2C%20on%20Thursday%2C%20May%2021%2C%202026%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32b403564c774507cd376a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETraffic%20snarling%20an%20interstate%20in%20California.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20remote-work%20era%20is%20over%2C%20and%20now%20we're%20living%20with%20the%20vicious%20commuting%20aftereffects.%20Americans%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftti.tamu.edu%2F2025%2F10%2Ftraffic-hits-record-high-as-commuters-rewrite-the-rush-hour%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eever%20before%20in%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20average%20of%2063%20hours%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%20and%20congestion%20has%20spread%20out%20throughout%20the%20day%20as%20more%20Americans%20head%20to%20and%20from%20work%20at%20odd%20hours.%20It%20turns%20out%20that%20there's%20no%20off-peak%20when%20everyone%20is%20commuting%20at%20all%20times%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWelcome%20to%20the%20never-ending%20rush%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECommuting%20has%20always%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-longest-commute-times-ranked-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20pretty%20bleak%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20modern%20work%20experience.%20The%20mean%20travel%20time%20reached%20a%20new%20high%20in%202019%2C%20with%20Americans%20spending%20an%20average%20of%2027.6%20minutes%20for%20a%20one-way%20trip%2C%20up%20from%2025%20in%202006.%20That%20data%20tracks%20workers%20aged%2016%20and%20older%20who%20don't%20work%20from%20home%20and%20looks%20at%20survey%20respondents'%20last%20week%20of%20commuting.%20In%20the%20year%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20record%20high%209.8%25%20of%20workers%20spent%20an%20hour%20or%20more%20commuting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20remote%20work%20shock.%20Commute%20times%20plunged%2C%20even%20as%20vaccines%20became%20more%20widespread%20and%20more%20folks%20started%20tentatively%20reentering%20their%20cubicles.%20Now%2C%20though%2C%20we're%20approaching%20those%20pre-pandemic%20peaks%3A%20In%202024%2C%20the%20average%20commute%20time%20rose%20to%2027.2%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20second%20highest%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWNnNh%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWNnNh%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20workers%20driving%20to%20work%20has%20ticked%20back%20up%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20although%20it's%20below%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%20Ultra-long%20commutes%20are%20also%20making%20a%20sharp%20comeback%2C%20with%209.3%25%20of%20workers%20traveling%20an%20hour%20or%20more%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sharp%20increase%20from%207.7%25%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FmtfDD%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FmtfDD%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EChalk%20some%20of%20that%20up%20to%20pandemic%20migration%20patterns.%20On%20the%20whole%2C%20folks%20moved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-high-earners-moved-office-work-from-home-remote-work-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efurther%20away%20from%20their%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20data%20shared%20with%20me%20by%20Stanford's%20work-from-home%20research%20team.%20A%20greater%20share%20of%20Americans%20now%20live%20more%20than%2050%20miles%20from%20the%20office%2C%20and%20the%20mean%20distance%20to%20work%20is%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20pre-pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDCk4v%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDCk4v%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20might%20be%20due%20to%20the%20kinds%20of%20homes%20Americans%20could%20afford%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20chaos%20of%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20Alex%20Thomas%2C%20a%20research%20manager%20at%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20Americans%20moving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-homes-built-patios-porches-heres-why-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einto%20new-build%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20spending%20longer%20on%20the%20road.%20%26quot%3BA%20new%20construction%20homebuyer%20typically%20commutes%20about%2010%20to%2015%25%20longer%20than%20the%20typical%20homeowner%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20told%20me.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20places%20where%20people%20can%20afford%20to%20buy%20(especially%20younger%20people%20looking%20for%20a%20deal)%20are%20much%20further%20from%20office%20hubs.%20Take%20ex-urban%20markets%20like%20Stockton%2C%20California%2C%20or%20Greeley%2C%20Colorado%2C%20for%20example.%20They're%20both%20tied%20to%20major%20employment%20hubs%2C%20the%20Bay%20Area%20and%20Denver%2C%20respectively%2C%20but%20offer%20much%20cheaper%2C%20newly-constructed%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20much%20longer%20commutes%20%E2%80%94%20than%20the%20core%20of%20those%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20notion%20of%20drive%20till%20you%20qualify%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20that's%20a%20little%20bit%20cheaper%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20further%20out%2C%20you're%20probably%20going%20to%20have%20to%20drive%20further%20to%20work%20or%20to%20cultural%20amenities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222130%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lana%20and%20Kelley%20with%20daughter%20Jenna%2C%20age%2012%2C%20were%20already%20anchored%20on%20the%20shoulder%20for%20two%20hours%20waiting%20for%20the%20traffic%20to%20ease.%20They%20were%20returning%20to%20Gypsum%20after%20at%20trip%20to%20Greeley%20and%20Nebraska%20for%20boating.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32b4a5564c774507cd3773%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20family%20waits%20out%20traffic%20after%20a%20trip%20to%20Greeley.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Brainerd%2FThe%20Denver%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20new%20construction%20buyers%20are%20cash-strapped.%20Some%20might%20be%20seeking%20a%20more%20luxurious%2C%20customizable%2C%20or%20spacious%20option.%20But%20for%20entry-level%20buyers%2C%20new%20homes%20offer%20affordability%20that%20other%20properties%20might%20not%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Thomas%20says%2C%20developers%20and%20builders%20will%20often%20offer%20incentives%20like%20mortgage%20rate%20buydowns%2C%20which%20help%20lower%20monthly%20payments%20considerably%20and%20help%20entry-level%20buyers%20get%20in%20the%20door.%20And%20moving%20far%20away%20is%20still%20worth%20it%20for%20new%20home%20buyers.%20Thomas%20found%20that%2C%20on%20average%2C%20they%20work%20from%20home%20more%20often%20than%20the%20typical%20homeowner%2C%20so%20while%20each%20trip%20may%20be%20longer%2C%20their%20total%20weekly%20commute%20time%20may%20even%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20many%20folks%20seem%20willing%20to%20make%20a%20longer%20commute%20trade-off%2C%20especially%20since%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-allow-work-from-home-fridays-boosts-businesses-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20more%20flexibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20baked%20into%20what%20was%20once%20a%20rigid%20routine.%20Michael%20Manville%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20urban%20planning%20at%20the%20UCLA%20Luskin%20School%20of%20Public%20Affairs%2C%20said%20it's%20possible%20a%20hefty%20chunk%20of%20white-collar%20workers%20would%20say%20that%20their%20commutes%20are%20better%20than%20before%2C%20simply%20because%20they%20hop%20behind%20the%20wheel%20or%20hoof%20it%20on%20the%20train%20less%20often.%20Maybe%20they're%20exposed%20to%20more%20congestion%20when%20they're%20on%20the%20road%2C%20but%20if%20they're%20not%20commuting%20daily%2C%20they%20mentally%20bake%20in%20the%20days%20they're%20not%20dealing%20with%20traffic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraffic-commuting-rush-hour-remote-work-from-home-new-york-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeveryone%20is%20on%20the%20road%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20the%20time%20now.%20If%20you%20work%20from%20home%20part-time%2C%20and%20your%20other%20neighbor%20does%20too%2C%20and%20then%20you%20both%20head%20out%20at%20an%20off%20hour%20for%20a%20long%20drive%2C%20you're%20now%20two%20more%20cars%20on%20the%20road.%20In%202019%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20Transportation%20Institute%2C%2070.5%25%20of%20weekday%20delays%20on%20national%20freeways%20happened%20during%20the%20morning%20and%20evening%20peaks%20%E2%80%94%20from%206-10%20a.m.%2C%20and%203-7%20p.m.%2C%20respectively.%20Around%205%25%20of%20that%20delay%20has%20shifted%20from%20peak%20periods%20into%20the%20midday%20hours%20of%2010%20a.m.-3%20p.m.%20The%20hours%20of%201%20p.m.%20and%202%20p.m.%20have%20seen%20marked%20increases%2C%20in%20particular.%20The%20magnitude%20of%20the%20delays%20is%20also%20greater%3B%20even%20if%20there's%20technically%20less%20share%20of%20delay%20during%20peak%20hours%2C%20commuters%20are%20still%20spending%20more%20time%20in%20traffic%20than%20they%20did%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20Carrie%20Weston%2C%2043%2C%20sits%20in%20her%20Minnesota%20office%2C%20she's%20constantly%20staring%20down%20at%20her%20afternoon%20fate.%20Her%20window%20overlooks%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-americas-widest-highways-why-expanding-wont-help-traffic-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20main%20highways%3C%2Fa%3E%20circling%20the%20city%2C%20giving%20her%20a%20real-time%20update%20on%20how%20snarled%20her%20road%20home%20will%20be.%20Weston%20is%20one%20of%20the%20flexible%20workers%20putting%20in%20long%20commuting%20hours%20(she%20drives%20at%20least%2045%20minutes%20one%20way%2C%20and%20that%20can%20stretch%20to%202.5%20hours%20depending%20on%20the%20weather).%20As%20a%20mom%20of%20six%2C%20she%20adds%20on%20drive%20time%20for%20after-school%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20traffic%20is%20bad%20or%20if%20there's%20an%20accident%2C%20it%20really%2C%20really%20impacts%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Weston%20says.%20According%20to%20the%20TAMU%20report%2C%20commuters%20across%20the%20country%20are%20accumulating%20a%20historic%20number%20of%20hours%20delayed%2C%20even%20as%20weekdays%20account%20for%20a%20smaller%20share%20of%20total%20delay.%20The%20endless%20rush%20hour%20is%20even%20snaking%20into%20the%20weekends%3A%20both%20Saturday%20and%20Sunday%20have%20a%20higher%20share%20of%20total%20delays%20than%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20family%20will%20be%20out%20and%20about%20on%20the%20weekends%2C%20and%20we're%20like%2C%20'Why%20is%20it%20stop-and-go%20traffic%20on%20a%20Saturday%20afternoon%3F'%26quot%3B%20Weston%20says.%20That%20could%20come%20from%20a%20slew%20of%20factors%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-good-for-productivity-here-to-stay-pwc-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epartial-remote%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20eager%20to%20get%20out%20of%20their%20houses%3B%20they%20live%20farther%20from%20the%20cultural%20or%20economic%20activities%20they%20enjoy%3B%20they%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20allocate%20that%20weekend%20time%20to%20errands%2C%20and%20can%20instead%20devote%20it%20to%20longer%20leisure%20trips.%20Add%20in%20all%20of%20the%20workers%20who%20have%20to%20go%20in%20on%20weekends%20%E2%80%94%20like%20service%20workers%2C%20or%20those%20in%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you've%20got%20a%20traffic%20jam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what's%20there%20to%20do%20about%20our%20now-omnipresent%20rush%20hour%3F%20It's%20possible%20that%20we're%20doomed%20to%20a%20traffic-infested%20country%20%E2%80%94%20the%20price%20we%20pay%20for%20that%20oh-so-valuable%20flexibility.%20But%20if%20we%20want%20to%20actually%20fight%20back%20against%20the%20ballooning%20time%20behind%20the%20wheel%2C%20there%20are%20options.%20One%20answer%3A%20scaling%20up%20public%20transportation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-new-yorkers-commute-and-who-commutes-subway-bus-driving-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York's%20subway%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20added%20more%20trains%20on%20busy%20express%20lines%20to%20accommodate%20shifting%20travel%20times%2C%20extending%20rush-hour%20service%20earlier%20and%20later%2C%20and%20removing%20trains%20from%20previously%20peak%20slots.%20But%20unless%20America%20dramatically%20revamps%20and%20builds%20a%20huge%20swath%20of%20public%20transportation%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20looking%20to%20the%20road%20%E2%80%94%20and%20putting%20that%20flexibility%20to%20good%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20crowded%20A%20train%20subway%20platform%2C%20March%2030%2C%202026%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32b5684074dae0e2044a72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20crowded%20A%20train%20subway%20platform%2C%20March%2030%2C%202026%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2F%20Corbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20we%20do%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20highways%20and%20urban%20areas%20are%20so%20congested%3F%26quot%3B%20Manville%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20that%20no%20one%20particularly%20likes%2C%20but%20the%20only%20one%20that's%20ever%20been%20shown%20to%20work%20at%20all%20is%2C%20you%20price%20those%20highways%20dynamically.%26quot%3B%20That%20would%20be%20a%20different%20model%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcongestion-pricing-is-squeezing-nyc-street-vendors-budgets-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflat%20congestion%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20but%20instead%20more%20akin%20to%20Singapore%3A%20Depending%20on%20how%20many%20people%20want%20to%20use%20the%20road%20at%20certain%20times%2C%20the%20price%20goes%20up%20or%20down%2C%20with%20pricing%20calibrated%20to%20keep%20the%20road%20moving%20between%2045%20and%2055%20miles%20an%20hour.%20When%20the%20road%20is%20moving%20faster%20than%20the%20target%20traffic%20flow%2C%20the%20pricing%20should%20drop%3B%20when%20it%20creeps%20above%20that%2C%20the%20pricing%20should%20go%20up%2C%20making%20drivers%20reconsider%20whether%20to%20take%20another%20route%20or%20wait%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20moderate%2C%20but%20still%20constant%2C%20rush%20hour%2C%20spreading%20out%20cars%20further%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20midday%20driving%20might%20become%20more%20prevalent%2C%20but%20will%20clear%20the%20road%20for%20those%20who%20have%20hard%20ins%20at%20the%20office%20(like%20service%20workers).%20It%20could%20end%20up%20being%20an%20accelerant%20of%20the%20current%20trend%2C%20spreading%20traffic%20out%20more%2C%20while%20also%20generating%20revenue%20for%20road%20maintenance%20and%20reducing%20wear%20and%20tear.%20Importantly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw26956%2Fw26956.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20one%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20forms%20of%20this%20pricing%20can%20offer%20something%20current%20traffic-dwellers%20crave%3A%20Knowing%20how%20long%20it'll%20take%20them%20to%20travel%20somewhere.%20Of%20course%2C%20that%20type%20of%20pricing%20can%20have%20its%20own%20drawbacks.%20For%20tradespeople%20or%20workers%20with%20set%20shift%20commutes%2C%20which%20might%20fall%20during%20the%20higher-priced%20times%20of%20day%2C%20the%20tax%20can%20fall%20regressively%20%E2%80%94%20an%20area%20where%2C%20Manville%20says%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20localities%20thinking%20about%20who%20to%20exempt%20from%20a%20potential%20levy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20first%20work-related%20reckoning%20of%20the%20pandemic%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20discovery%20that%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20feasible%2C%20maybe%20its%20subsequent%20flexibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20high-traffic%20situations%20it%20brings%20%E2%80%94%20can%20spark%20a%20new%20reckoning%20about%20how%20and%20when%20we%20get%20to%20where%20we're%20going.%20We're%20all%20sharing%20the%20road%20(or%20subway)%20together%20a%20lot%20more%3B%20maybe%20that%20commuting%20visibility%20can%20spark%20a%20larger%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjuliana-kaplan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJuliana%20Kaplan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20the%20economy%20team%2C%20where%20she%20covers%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20kitchen%20table%20economics%2C%20and%20the%20people%20behind%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnever-ending-rush-hour-remote-work-flexible-schedules-commutes-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782117482000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3453800e60dfb3f373f58c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fne